cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with material classification in natural settings using Convolutional Neural Networks (convnets). Additionally, the use of transfer learning from object recognition tasks suggests a focus on computer vision. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The analysis of reflectance and shading information could also suggest a Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the mention of a new dataset could place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
